</code></pre></div></div> <p>My first visit at the <a href="https://www.iac.es">IAC</a>. See <a href="https://shorturl.at/0N43C">here</a> for reference!</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="sample-posts"/><category term="research"/><category term="training"/><category term="experiences"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[First part of my visiting fellow period at IAC]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Observation School in La Palma, Canary Islands</title><link href="https://apersici.github.io/blog/2024/photo-gallery2/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Observation School in La Palma, Canary Islands"/><published>2024-06-12T01:59:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-06-12T01:59:00+00:00</updated><id>https://apersici.github.io/blog/2024/photo-gallery2</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://apersici.github.io/blog/2024/photo-gallery2/"><![CDATA[<p>Last july, I had the chance to attend the Observation School hosted at the Observatorio del Roque de los Muchachos (ORM).<br/> The focus was on an intensive, practice-oriented training programme in astronomical observation and data analysis.</p> <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Take a look at some of the images I took during the observing school!
</code></pre></div></div> <hr/> <div class="spotlight-group"> <a class="spotlight" href="/assets/img/roque2.jpg"> <img src="/assets/img/roque2.jpg" alt="Photo 1" style="width: 150px; height: auto;"/> </a> <a class="spotlight" href="/assets/img/roque1.jpg"> <img src="/assets/img/roque1.jpg" alt="Photo 2" style="width: 150px; height: auto;"/> </a> <a class="spotlight" href="/assets/img/roque3.jpg"> <img src="/assets/img/roque3.jpg" alt="Photo 3" style="width: 150px; height: auto;"/> </a> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="research"/><category term="images"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Observation school in La Palma]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">AstroAI workshop at the Center for Astrophysics, Harvard &amp;amp; Smithsonian</title><link href="https://apersici.github.io/blog/2024/harvard/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="AstroAI workshop at the Center for Astrophysics, Harvard &amp;amp; Smithsonian"/><published>2024-06-12T01:59:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-06-12T01:59:00+00:00</updated><id>https://apersici.github.io/blog/2024/harvard</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://apersici.github.io/blog/2024/harvard/"><![CDATA[<p><img src="assets/img/astroai.png" alt="Horizontal image" style="width: 100%; max-width: 800px;"/></p> <p>Last july, I attended the <a href="https://astroai.cfa.harvard.edu/workshop/details.html">AstroAI workshop</a> at the <a href="https://www.cfa.harvard.edu">Center for Astrophysics, Harvard &amp; Smithsonian</a> in Boston, USA. The workshop spanned over the course of five days, with a series of lectures and discussions led by experts in the fields of AI/ML and astrophysics, hands on sessions, talks by early career scientists in the field, and networking events.</p> <p>I had the chance to present my poster titled: <em>Blended Source Detection in Deep Fields: A Max-Tree Approach Informed by Survey and Simulated Data</em>. :smile:</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="research"/><category term="images"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[AstroAI is a project led by Dr. Cecilia Garraffo in the Center for Astrophysics, Harvard & Smithsonian]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">ESAC Open Day</title><link href="https://apersici.github.io/blog/2023/openday/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="ESAC Open Day"/><published>2023-10-21T09:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2023-10-21T09:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://apersici.github.io/blog/2023/openday</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://apersici.github.io/blog/2023/openday/"><![CDATA[<p>The European Space Astronomy Centre (ESAC) opened its doors on October 21st for a fantastic <a href="https://www.esa.int/About_Us/ESAC/Get_set_for_the_ESA_Open_Day_2023_at_ESAC">Open Day</a>!</p> <p>I got the chance to talk (in Spanish!) about variable objects in the <a href="https://www.esa.int/Science_Exploration/Space_Science/Gaia">Gaia</a> Mission during the<br/> <em>Científico por un día</em> session, as part of the ESA crew.</p> <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Take a look at some of the pictures from the Open Day:
